{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Replace use of hotels for asylum seekers with a risk-based accommodation system",
        "additional_details": "The Government should introduce primary legislation to replace long-term use of hotels for asylum seeker accommodation with a risk-based processing system. This should include rapid individual assessment, time-limited decisions, differentiated accommodation based on risk and vulnerability, and designated UK-controlled processing facilities for cases with unresolved identity or security concerns, subject to judicial oversight.",
        "background": "The Government should introduce legislation to replace long-term use of hotels for asylum seeker accommodation with a risk-based processing system, including rapid assessment, time-limited decisions, and UK-controlled processing facilities where identity or security concerns remain unresolved.",
